cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in digital pathology, specifically for tumor localization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a modified transition module for CNNs, which involves learning global average pooling layers from filters of varying sizes to encourage class-specific filters at multiple spatial resolutions. This modification is related to the architecture of the neural network, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing complex images in digital pathology, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves training the neural network on two independent datasets, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
